init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look around and see a swarm of bees, all bowing to you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "We are at your service, Your Majesty," said the bees, bowing low.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well," said the princess, "I would like some honey for my tea."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "We're sorry, Your Majesty," said the bees.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well, I don't want you to sting me," said the princess.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I wonder what else I can order them to do," said the princess.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I've decided," said the princess, "that I want to go for a walk in the garden."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Right away, Your Majesty," said the bees.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "What would you like, Your Majesty?" asked the bees.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She smiled as the bees buzzed around her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: and said "I'm so glad I have you."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were happy to serve the princess.
